2.10	UN_Committee_on_the_Rights_of_the_Child	Committee on the Rights of the Child	The Committee on the Rights of the Child (CRC) is a body of independent experts that monitors and reports on implementation of the United Nations Convention on the Rights of the Child by governments that ratify the Convention. The Committee also monitors implementation of the optional protocol on the involvement of children in armed conflict and the optional protocol on the sale of children, child prostitution and child pornography (OP-SC).	
